rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description:
A broadcaster that transmits primarily audio content (though some metadata may also be transmitted) via radio waves, satellite or the internet.
Things that are radio stations:
## Terrestrial radio stations (e.g. KITS).
## Satellite radio stations (e.g.: SIRIUS XMU).
## Internet radio stations (e.g.: WOXY).
Things that are NOT radio stations:
## TV based audio streams (e.g.: Channel 907, Throwback Jamz, on Comcast Digital TV). These are instances of mso:broadcast.tv_station.
## Internet radio feeds (e.g.: KITS 32kbps stream). These are instances of mso:broadcast.internet_stream.
## The content which is broadcast by a radio station (e.g.: Live 105 - KITS). This should be typed as mso:broadcast.content and linked to the station.
## Services that provide custom or individualized audio streams (e.g.: Pandora).
